Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri The remains of a female undergraduate of the Federal Polytechnic, Nekede, Owerri, Imo State, Cynthia Obieshi, who died after an alleged sex romp with her boyfriend, Samuel Osuji, were on Thursday interred. The 25-year-old was buried at her father’s compound in the Umuaro II Autonomous Community in the Isiala Mbano Local Government Area of the state amidst tears. PUNCH Metro had reported that the corpses of the two lovers were on Sunday morning found in a room at a hostel after they had allegedly indulged in a sex romp. The police spokesperson in the state, Orlando Okeokwu, had told our correspondent that the corpses were deposited in a morgue. He had said, “On Sunday, June 14, 2020, acting on a report received at the police station, operatives of the Divisional Police Headquarters, Nekede/Ihiagwa, moved to Room 19, Vic-Mic Lodge, situated around the JMJ bus stop, broke into the room and found the lifeless bodies of one Cynthia Obieshi and one Samuel Osuji. “It was gathered that the said Cynthia visited her boyfriend, Samuel, on June 13, 2020, and passed the night in his room, but unfortunately, both of them couldn’t wake up the next morning. “Preliminary investigation suggests that the diseased persons might have died as a result of drug consumption.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 